  "prompt": "Does UWO give a 4% boost to high school students applying from Alberta?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the University of Western Ontario (UWO), also known as Western University, does not have a standardized 4% boost for all high school students applying from Alberta. However, Western University does use a conversion scale to translate the grading systems of different provinces into a consistent metric for admissions purposes. Alberta uses a percentage-based grading system, so the university will convert these percentages to assess eligibility for admission.\n\nWestern University\u2019s admissions process is holistic, meaning they consider multiple factors beyond just grades, such as extracurricular activities, personal statements, and course rigor. If there were specific adjustments or boosts to Alberta grades in the past, they would likely be outlined in the university's official admissions website or materials.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend checking Western University\u2019s official admissions website or contacting their admissions office directly. They can clarify whether any specific adjustments apply to Alberta applicants for the current admissions cycle.",
